docs.abstract: The former vice president is preparing his 2020 kickoff, securing staff and alerting top Democrats he plans to run. But he hasn’t made a final decision yet.
docs.snippet: The former vice president is preparing his 2020 kickoff, securing staff and alerting top Democrats he plans to run. But he hasn’t made a final decision yet.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The pieces for a Joseph R. Biden Jr. presidential campaign are falling into place: His nucleus of advisers has begun offering campaign positions to seasoned Democratic strategists. They are eyeing a headquarters in Delaware or nearby Philadelphia and a launch date in the beginning of April. Mr. Biden’s family is on board — his wife, Jill, enthusiastically so.

headline.main: Joe Biden’s 2020 Plan Is Almost Complete. Democrats Are Impatient.
headline.print_headline: Plan in Place, Biden’s Army Awaits Biden
